New Features and Important Changes in GammaLib 00-04-09

Author(s) : Juergen Knoedlseder

July 8th, 2011


1. Introduction
---------------
This document briefly summarizes module by module the most important changes made since the last release of GammaLib.


2. Configuration
-----------------
Remove pkg-config usage from configure.ac as this introduced somas
on Mac OS X systems (by default there is no pkg-config on Mac OS X).

Add --enable-nan-check option and add option configuration information
to configuration summary screen dump.

Test for presence of Python.h and build Python binding only if the
file exists. This should resolve installation issues on systems that
do not have the Python development package installed.


3. Application module
---------------------
None


4. FITS I/O Interface
---------------------
None


5. Linear algebra module
------------------------
None


6. Model module
---------------
Add NaN/Inf check to various spatial and spectral models.


7. Numerics module
------------------
Add NaN/Inf check to GIntegral class.


8. Observation module
---------------------
Add NaN/Inf check to GResponse and GObservation class.


9. Optimization module
----------------------
None


10. Sky module
--------------
Replaced the IDL based World Coordinate System code by wcslib based code.
This improves performance and accuracy of the coordinate transformation
and corrects a bug in the LONPOLE/LATPOLE keywords that were written in
the earlier version into the FITS file.

Introduced GWcslib base class for projections that are wcslib based.
All code adapted from wcslib goes into that class. Not all functionality
has yet been ported from wcslib to GammaLib, but the essential things
for creating, writing and reading WCS compliant FITS files is there.

Introduced a World Coordinate System registry for easy extension of the
set of projections.

Added the following projection types: AZP, STG, TAN


11. Support module
------------------
None


